      </p>

     </div>
     <span class="pb center" title="page number in print edition" id="ADMS-06-02-02-pb-0391">[391<a style="padding-left: 0px" onclick="window.open('/img-document-get.xqy?image=ADMS/Pages/ADMS-06-02/ADMS-06-02-02-pb-0391.jpg', 'pageImage', 'scrollbars=1,resizable=1'); return false" onkeypress="this.onclick();" tabindex="0" title="Click to view image of page from print edition"><img src="/img-ML/page-icon.gif" width="18" height="20" style="vertical-align:middle;" alt="page icon"/></a>]</span>
     <div id="fn" class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#PJA02d105n1-ptr" id="PJA02d105n1">1</a>
      
   <p>Nicholas Boileau Despraux (16361711), French literary critic, poet, and satirist (<span class="ref-st" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ J. C. F. Hoefer, ed., &lt;i&gt;Nouvelle biographic gnrale depuis les temps les plus reculs jusqu' nos jours&lt;/i&gt;, Paris, 18521866; 46 vols. ]">Hoefer, <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Nouv. biog. gnrale</span></span>).</p>

     </div>
     <div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#PJA02d105n2-ptr" id="PJA02d105n2">2</a>
      
   <p>Mercy Warrens <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">The Group.</span></p>

     </div>
     <div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#PJA02d105n3-ptr" id="PJA02d105n3">3</a>
      
   <p><a href="default.xqy?keys=ADMS-print-06-02-02-0067" class="document">3 Jan. 1775</a>, above.</p>

     </div>
     <div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#PJA02d105n4-ptr" id="PJA02d105n4">4</a>
      
   <p>A reference to the Second Provincial Congress, in which Mrs. Warren, like her husband, assumed that <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ John Adams (17351826) ]">JA</abbr> would have a seat.</p>

     </div>
     <div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#PJA02d105n5-ptr" id="PJA02d105n5">5</a>
      
   <p>The place of meeting of the Second Provincial Congress.</p>

